## 5. Dependency Sorting

Dependencies in `.gradle.kts` files MUST be alphabetically sorted within each configuration block.

```kotlin
// BAD — unsorted
dependencies {
    implementation(libs.hilt.android)
    implementation(libs.androidx.core.ktx)
    implementation(libs.compose.foundation)
}

// GOOD — alphabetically sorted within each block
dependencies {
    implementation(libs.androidx.core.ktx)
    implementation(libs.compose.foundation)
    implementation(libs.hilt.android)

    testImplementation(libs.assertk)
    testImplementation(libs.junit)
    testImplementation(libs.turbine)
}
```

- Run `./gradlew sortDependencies` to auto-sort
- Run `./gradlew checkSortDependencies` to verify

---

## 6. Dependency Management

ALL dependency versions are managed in `gradle/libs.versions.toml`.

```kotlin
// BAD — hardcoded version
implementation("androidx.core:core-ktx:1.16.0")

// GOOD — version catalog reference
implementation(libs.androidx.core.ktx)
```

**When adding a new dependency:**
1. Add the version to `[versions]` in `gradle/libs.versions.toml`
2. Add the library entry to `[libraries]`
3. Reference via `libs.<alias>` in the `.gradle.kts` file
4. Keep the entry alphabetically sorted

**buildHealth enforces:**
- No unused dependencies (`severity: fail`)
- No unused annotation processors (`severity: fail`)
- No redundant plugins (`severity: fail`)
- Correct dependency configurations — use `implementation` vs `api` vs `compileOnly` correctly (`severity: fail`)
- Remove a dependency if you remove the code that uses it

---

## 7. Android Lint

- Android Lint must pass: `./gradlew lint`
- Do NOT introduce new lint warnings
- Existing issues are tracked in module-level `lint-baseline.xml` files — do NOT modify baselines
- Fix lint issues in your code rather than suppressing or baselining them

